About me

Professional

I first experienced STEM data science while clustering molecular-dynamics simulations of proteins from Folding@home. Since then, I have had the privilege of improving my mass-spectrometry, software engineering, and statistical knowledge in Oliver Fiehn’s lab as well as at the Chan Zuckerberg Biohub. I am interested in any research where I can deploy modern technology to have a tangible impact, so I’m looking forward to any data challenges that come my way.

Personal

I like to spend an inordinate amount of free time wrangling three cats: Opal, Data, and One-ounce. When I get the chance, I try to go hiking and drink coffee with family and friends.
